    {
        "content": "<p>kpshek <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94#issuecomment-343057789\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94#issuecomment-343057789\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94\">PR #94</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-email=\"jmandel@gmail.com\" data-user-id=\"9\">@Josh Mandel</span> - I just added support for code syntax highlighting by simply enabling the <a href=\"https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/getting-started/#extensions\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/getting-started/#extensions\">recommended Material extensions</a>, one of them being the syntax highlighter. Take another look! <img alt=\"ðŸ˜„\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"/static/generated/emoji/images/emoji/unicode/1f604.png\" title=\"ðŸ˜„\"></p>\n</blockquote>",
