    {
        "content": "<p>kpshek <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94#issuecomment-343169052\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94#issuecomment-343169052\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/94\">PR #94</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is the data model in swagger up-to-date? Wondering if we should keep/remove.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We have the Swagger API in a separate repository (<a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/api\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/api\">api</a>) right now. However, I want to move the YAML file into this repository and make it part of our site/specification. This will make it easier to keep it up-to-date with any changes we do in the future.</p>\n<p>I will do that as soon as this gets merged to master.</p>\n</blockquote>",
